Both required files are written and the transcript validates against the schema (25 iterations, 38 hypotheses, 38 analyses).

**Headline finding:** `treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine` increases `objective_response` only in patients who are `unfit_for_intensive=1` AND `npm1_mutation=1` AND `tp53_mutation=0` AND `complex_karyotype=0`. In that 9% subgroup OR rises from ~16% to ~79% (logit interaction p=1.2e-291); outside it VEN/AZA has no detectable effect. No other treatment (7+3, midostaurin, gilteritinib, ivosidenib, enasidenib) shows a meaningful effect on response in any subgroup — the canonical FLT3/IDH-inhibitor biomarker interactions are absent in this cohort.
